SAMPLE-EXTRACT_PROTOCOL_CH1_41: RNAs were extracted from tissue using RNAiso Plus (Takara Bio Inc.), followed by purification using RNeasy MinElute (Qiagen Inc.). RNAs were assessed for quality and was quantified using an RNA 6000 Nano LabChip on a 2100 Bioanalyzer (Agilent Inc.).
SAMPLE-DATA_PROCESSING_43: Illumina Casava1.8 software used for basecalling.
SAMPLE-DATA_PROCESSING_44: RNA sequencing reads were aligned to the NCBI human reference genome assembly (build 37.1) using GSNAP (Wu and Nacu, Bioinformatics, 2010) with allowance for 5% mismatches.
SAMPLE-DATA_PROCESSING_45: RNA sequencing reads were also aligned to a cDNA set consisting of 161,250 mRNA sequences obtained from public databases (36,742 RefSeq, 73,671 UCSC, and 161,214 Ensembl) to decrease the false positives and false negatives in variant detection from RNA sequencing data (Ju et al., Nature Genetics, 2011; Ju et al., Genome Researcg, 2012).
SAMPLE-DATA_PROCESSING_46: For each gene, the number of reads aligned to it (raw read count) was normalized by RPKM (reads per kilobase per million mapped reads) (Mortazavi et al., Nature Methods, 2008).
